{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "When some music festival fans quit drinking or taking drugs, they thought they would have to give up the gatherings, but safe spots at some festivals offer support.", "abstract": "Volunteers have been creating support communities for sober people at large summer music festivals, which are notorious for prevalence of drug and alcohol abuse; growing movement, inspired by group of Grateful Dead fans in 1980s and driven by social media, is welcomed and aided by festival promoters, who want to counter negative press following handful of publicized drug overdoses.", "section_name": "Arts", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Joe", "role": "reported", "lastname": "COSCARELLI", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By JOE COSCARELLI"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/04/arts/music/raving-sober-remembering-last-night-in-the-morning.html", "lead_paragraph": "When some music festival fans quit drinking or taking drugs, they thought they would have to give up the gatherings, but safe spots at some festivals offer support.", "headline": {"main": "Remembering Last Night\u2019s Music Festival in the Morning", "print_headline": "Raving Sober"}, "_id": "556ec21c38f0d83db8478a08", "word_count": "1210", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/06/03/arts/04SOBERBALLWEB1/04SOBERBALLWEB1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/06/03/arts/04SOBERBALLWEB1/04SOBERBALLWEB1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2015/06/03/arts/04SOBERBALLWEB1/04SOBERBALLWEB1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/06/03/arts/04SOBERBALLWEB1/04SOBERBALLWEB1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/06/03/arts/04SOBERBALLWEB1/04SOBERBALLWEB1-thumbStandard.jpg", "leg